<H2>States with Family Rules and Laws</H2>

Thirteen states currently allow victims' families to watch the execution of the killers of their relatives. The laws restrict access to immediate family members and some limit the number who can attend.<p>

These states guarantee families the right to watch.<p>
Oklahoma<br>
Washington<p>

Administrative hearings are held in these states to determine access.<p>

California<br>
Florida<br>
Illinois *<br>
Louisiana<br>
Montana<br>
North Carolina<br>
Ohio<br>
Pennsylvania<br>
Texas<br>
Utah<br>
Virginia<p>

* Illinois allows families to watch only through closed-circuit television.<p>

