In a celebrated, though less complicated, recent example, a grand
jury decided against indicting Dr. Timothy Quill, who admitted in
the pages of the New England Journal of Medicine that he had
intentionally prescribed the barbiturates that a terminally ill
patient used to end her life. Pugliese, supra note 46, at 1298 n.
47.

