who administered a lethal injection to a comatose patient was
acquitted of assisted suicide. In 1950, another doctor was
acquitted after injecting a "fatal air embolism into the blood
vessels of a carcinoma patient, who had repeatedly urged him to
end her misery." Id. at 1298 nn. 45-46.

