Misc.2d 67 (Ohio Mun. 1995); People v. Kevorkian, 527 N.W.2d 714
(Mich. 1994), cert. denied, 115 S.Ct. 1795 (1995) (holding that
Dr. Kevorkian may be prosecuted either under a Michigan
statute--held to be constitutional--or under the common-law felony
of assisting suicide); People v. Duffy, 185 A.D.2d 371, 586
